## Working with NULL
NULL means 'no value' — it's different from 0 or empty string.

```sql
-- Check for NULL
SELECT * FROM users WHERE phone IS NULL;
SELECT * FROM users WHERE phone IS NOT NULL;

-- COALESCE: provide default for NULL
SELECT name, COALESCE(phone, 'N/A') AS phone
FROM users;

-- IFNULL (SQLite specific)
SELECT name, IFNULL(phone, 'Unknown') FROM users;
```

